race.comment: DASHING DOUBLE (8) did well last start but found a couple better over this trip at Gosford, only beaten a tick over a length in third. Strips rock-hard fit and doesn't need to improve much to get the job done. ROYAL CHIC (12) never looked likely last time at Goulburn when getting a mile back but was strong late. Will appreciate the added trip and could take some stopping if they can utilise her low draw. SIR TUA (10) was popular in betting last time out but didn't live up to market expectations, finishing fifth at Canberra. Strips fitter and can bounce back sharply over the mile. ROYSTON (3) warmed nicely late when resuming at Hawkesbury. Is sure to have come on from that but is likely to get back again from the draw. Watch for him late. WHAT SHE'S HAVING (13) was at long odds on debut last time out and finished fifth, only beaten 2 lengths, over 1400m here. Is a likely improver and gets a key booking in Boudvillain. Don't dismiss.
